usdPimMIB.name: usdPimMIB
usdPimMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPimMIB.description: The enterprise MIB module for management of PIM routers.

UsdPimType.name: UsdPimType
UsdPimType.description: This data type is used do identify Sparse mode and Dense mode PIM protocol.

usdPimNumHelloRcvd.name: usdPimNumHelloRcvd
usdPimNumHelloRcvd.description: Total number of Hellos received by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumJoinPruneRcvd.name: usdPimNumJoinPruneRcvd
usdPimNumJoinPruneRcvd.description: Total number of JoinPrunes received by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumAssertRcvd.name: usdPimNumAssertRcvd
usdPimNumAssertRcvd.description: Total number of Asserts received by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumGraftRcvd.name: usdPimNumGraftRcvd
usdPimNumGraftRcvd.description: Total number of Grafts received by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumGraftAckRcvd.name: usdPimNumGraftAckRcvd
usdPimNumGraftAckRcvd.description: Total number of Graft Acks received by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumHelloSent.name: usdPimNumHelloSent
usdPimNumHelloSent.description: Total number of Hellos sent by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumJoinPruneSent.name: usdPimNumJoinPruneSent
usdPimNumJoinPruneSent.description: Total number of JoinPrunes sent by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumAssertSent.name: usdPimNumAssertSent
usdPimNumAssertSent.description: Total number of Asserts sent by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumGraftSent.name: usdPimNumGraftSent
usdPimNumGraftSent.description: Total number of Grafts sent by PIM on this router.

usdPimNumGraftAckSent.name: usdPimNumGraftAckSent
usdPimNumGraftAckSent.description: Total number of Graft Acks sent by PIM on this router.

usdPimInterfaceTable.name: usdPimInterfaceTable
usdPimInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing enterprise specific information on a subset of the rows of the pimInterfaceTable defined in the standard PIM MIB.

usdPimInterfaceEntry.name: usdPimInterfaceEntry
usdPimInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimInterfaceTable. There is one entry per entry in the pimInterfaceTable.

usdPimIntfNumHelloRcvd.name: usdPimIntfNumHelloRcvd
usdPimIntfNumHelloRcvd.description: Total number of Hellos received by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneRcvd.name: usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneRcvd
usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneRcvd.description: Total number of JoinPrunes received by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumAssertRcvd.name: usdPimIntfNumAssertRcvd
usdPimIntfNumAssertRcvd.description: Total number of Asserts received by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumGraftRcvd.name: usdPimIntfNumGraftRcvd
usdPimIntfNumGraftRcvd.description: Total number of Grafts received by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumGraftAckRcvd.name: usdPimIntfNumGraftAckRcvd
usdPimIntfNumGraftAckRcvd.description: Total number of Graft Acks received by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumHelloSent.name: usdPimIntfNumHelloSent
usdPimIntfNumHelloSent.description: Total number of Hellos sent by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneSent.name: usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneSent
usdPimIntfNumJoinPruneSent.description: Total number of JoinPrunes sent by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumAssertSent.name: usdPimIntfNumAssertSent
usdPimIntfNumAssertSent.description: Total number of Asserts sent by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumGraftSent.name: usdPimIntfNumGraftSent
usdPimIntfNumGraftSent.description: Total number of Grafts sent by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfNumGraftAckSent.name: usdPimIntfNumGraftAckSent
usdPimIntfNumGraftAckSent.description: Total number of Graft Acks sent by PIM on this interface. It can only be cleared to 0 when doing set. Setting this also sets counters for other types of packets to 0.

usdPimIntfVersion.name: usdPimIntfVersion
usdPimIntfVersion.description: The version of PIM running on this interface.

usdPimIntfNumNbrs.name: usdPimIntfNumNbrs
usdPimIntfNumNbrs.description: Number of PIM neighbors detected on this interface.

usdPimMRouteTable.name: usdPimMRouteTable
usdPimMRouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing PIM multicast routing information describing its <*, *, RP>/ <*, G>/ <S, G> states.

usdPimMRouteEntry.name: usdPimMRouteEntry
usdPimMRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimMRouteTable.

usdPimMRouteGroup.name: usdPimMRouteGroup
usdPimMRouteGroup.description: The group address. Specified as 224.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> entries.

usdPimMRouteSource.name: usdPimMRouteSource
usdPimMRouteSource.description: The source address. Specified as 0.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteSourceMask.name: usdPimMRouteSourceMask
usdPimMRouteSourceMask.description: The source address mask. Specified as 255.255.255.255 for <S, G> entries and 0.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteRPAddress.name: usdPimMRouteRPAddress
usdPimMRouteRPAddress.description: The RP address used for <*, *, RP>. Specified as 0.0.0.0 for <S, G> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer.name: usdPimMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer
usdPimMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer.description: The time remaining before the router changes its upstream neighbor back to its RPF neighbor. This timer is called the Assert timer in the PIM Sparse and Dense mode specification. A value of 0 indicates that no Assert has changed the upstream neighbor away from the RPF neighbor.

usdPimMRouteAssertMetric.name: usdPimMRouteAssertMetric
usdPimMRouteAssertMetric.description: The metric advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or 0 if no such assert is in received.

usdPimMRouteAssertPref.name: usdPimMRouteAssertPref
usdPimMRouteAssertPref.description: The preference advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or 0 if no such assert is in effect.

usdPimMRouteAssertRPTBit.name: usdPimMRouteAssertRPTBit
usdPimMRouteAssertRPTBit.description: The value of the RPT-bit advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or false if no such assert is in effect.

usdPimMRouteBits.name: usdPimMRouteBits
usdPimMRouteBits.description: This object describes whether the entry is on shared tree (rpt) or shortest path tree (spt).

usdPimMRouteRPAddrInUse.name: usdPimMRouteRPAddrInUse
usdPimMRouteRPAddrInUse.description: The RP Address being used for the <S, G>RPT/<*, G>/<*, *, RP> entries. Set to 0.0.0.0 for <S, G> entries on shortest path tree.

usdPimMRouteUpstreamNbr.name: usdPimMRouteUpstreamNbr
usdPimMRouteUpstreamNbr.description: The address of upstream neighbor being used for the entry. Its set to 0.0.0.0 if the router is directly attached to source on one of its interface.

usdPimMRouteIifAddr.name: usdPimMRouteIifAddr
usdPimMRouteIifAddr.description: The address of incoming interface for this entry.

usdPimMRouteIsWaitingToSwitchToSPT.name: usdPimMRouteIsWaitingToSwitchToSPT
usdPimMRouteIsWaitingToSwitchToSPT.description: This object describes whether the entry is still waiting to switch completely to shortest path tree in case of <S, G> entries. It waits to do this till it receives first packet from incoming interface towards shortest path tree.

usdPimMRouteEntryExpiryTimer.name: usdPimMRouteEntryExpiryTimer
usdPimMRouteEntryExpiryTimer.description: The time after which the entry timer expires for this entry. Set to 0 if entry timer is not active.

usdPimMRouteSenderDRAddr.name: usdPimMRouteSenderDRAddr
usdPimMRouteSenderDRAddr.description: The address of the designated router on the sender's subnet in case of <S, G> entries. The sender designated router register encapsulates data to RP. Set to 0.0.0.0 for <*, G> and <*, *, RP> entries.

usdPimMRouteRouteAddr.name: usdPimMRouteRouteAddr
usdPimMRouteRouteAddr.description: The address of the route being used to do RPF check for this entry. It is set to 0.0.0.0 (with usdPimMRouteRouteMask set to 255.255.255.255) if there is no route available.

usdPimMRouteRouteMask.name: usdPimMRouteRouteMask
usdPimMRouteRouteMask.description: The mask of the route being used to do RPF check for this entry. It is set to 255.255.255.255 (with usdPimMRouteRoute set to 0.0.0.0) if there is no route available.

usdPimMRouteGRPAddr.name: usdPimMRouteGRPAddr
usdPimMRouteGRPAddr.description: The address of the group-to-RP mapping being used to get the RP for this entry. It is set to 0.0.0.0 (with usdPimMRouteGRPMask set to 0.0.0.0) if there is no group-to-RP mapping available or if entry is <*, *, RP>.

usdPimMRouteGRPMask.name: usdPimMRouteGRPMask
usdPimMRouteGRPMask.description: The mask of the group-to-RP mapping being used to get the RP for this entry. It is set to 255.255.255.255 (with usdPimMRouteGRPAddr set to 0.0.0.0) if there is no group-to-RP mapping available or if entry is <*, *, RP>.

usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeAll.name: usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeAll
usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeAll.description: This object indicates if some other multicast protocol is also interested in receiving data for this entry as a result of its interest in receiving all data. This will be particularly true for dense mode protocols which would want all data (<*, *>) from PIM sparse mode protocol.

usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeG.name: usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeG
usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeG.description: This object indicates if some other multicast protocol is also interested in receiving data for this entry as a result of its interest in receiving data for a given group. This will be particularly true for IGMP which would want data for a given group (<*, G>) from PIM protocol.

usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeSG.name: usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeSG
usdPimMRouteOtherProtoOifJoinTypeSG.description: This object indicates if some other multicast protocol is also interested in receiving data for this entry as a result of its interest in receiving data for a given <source, group>. This will be particularly true for IGMPv3 which would want data for a given <source, group (<S, G>) from PIM sparse-mode protocol.

usdPimMRoutePimType.name: usdPimMRoutePimType
usdPimMRoutePimType.description: This object indicates if the owner of this entry is Sparse mode or Dense mode PIM. Owner is usually determined by the protocol running on the incoming interface of the entry. In case sparse-dense mode PIM is running on the incoming interface, sparse-mode is the owner if RP for the group is known, else dense mode is the owner.

usdPimMRouteNextHopTable.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopTable
usdPimMRouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing PIM multicast routing information describing its <*, *, RP>/ <*, G>/ <S, G> outgoing interfaces.

usdPimMRouteNextHopEntry.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopEntry
usdPimMRouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimMRouteNextHopTable.

usdPimMRouteNextHopGroupAddr.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopGroupAddr
usdPimMRouteNextHopGroupAddr.description: The group address. Specified as 224.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> entries.

usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcAddr.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcAddr
usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcAddr.description: The source address. Specified as 0.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcMask.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcMask
usdPimMRouteNextHopSrcMask.description: The source address mask. Specified as 255.255.255.255 for <S, G> entries and 0.0.0.0 for <*, *, RP> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteNextHopRPAddr.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopRPAddr
usdPimMRouteNextHopRPAddr.description: The RP address used for <*, *, RP>. Specified as 0.0.0.0 for <S, G> and <*, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteNextHopIfId.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopIfId
usdPimMRouteNextHopIfId.description: The interface index of the outgoing interface (next hop). Specified as 0 for register outgoing interface. Register outgoing interfaces are created by DR on the source subnet to send PIM register encapsulated data (as unicast) to RP. It is also used by PIM boundary routers (PMBRs) to register data to RP.

usdPimMRouteNextHopAddress.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopAddress
usdPimMRouteNextHopAddress.description: This object takes following different values based on the type of next hop. It should be set to the address of RP in case the next hop interface is register interface i.e. usdPimMRouteNextHopIfId object is set to 0. It should be set to the address of neighbor in case the interface is an NBMA interface. In all other cases it should be set to the group address itself.

usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneReason.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneReason
usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneReason.description: This object indicates why the downstream interface was pruned, whether in response to a PIM prune message or due to PIM Assert processing.

usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSSRP.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSSRP
usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSSRP.description: This object indicates whether or not the interface was added as a result of receiving <*, *, RP> join in case of <*, *, RP> entry OR inherited as outgoing interface from corresponding <*, *, RP> entry in case of <*, G> entry.

usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeG.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeG
usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeG.description: This object indicates whether or not the interface was added as a result of receiving <*, G> join in case of <*, G> entry OR inherited as outgoing interface from corresponding <*, G> entry in case of <S, G> entry.

usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSG.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSG
usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinTypeSG.description: This object indicates whether or not the interface was added as a result of receiving <S, G> join in case of <S, G> entry.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasLGM.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasLGM
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasLGM.description: This object indicates whether or not the interface has local group membership (as indicated by IGMP) in case of <*, G> and <S, G> entries.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifAW.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifAW
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifAW.description: This object indicates whether or not this interface is the winner of assert for corresponding <*, G>/<S, G> entry.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifSendAssert.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifSendAssert
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifSendAssert.description: This object indicates whether or not this interface is going to send an assert at the end of assert suppression interval. Assert suppression is used to prevent a flood of assert to be generated in response to data or other asserts.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifRegister.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifRegister
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifRegister.description: This object indicates whether or not this next hop is a register outgoing interface.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifBorderBit.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifBorderBit
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifBorderBit.description: This object is used to describe a register outgoing interface. It indicates whether or not the border bit is set in the register packet when the packet is sent over the register interface. For all other (non-register) interfaces its set to false.

usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifNullEncapsBit.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifNullEncapsBit
usdPimMRouteNextHopHasOifNullEncapsBit.description: This object is used to describe a register outgoing interface. It indicates whether or not the NULL encapsulation bit is set (periodically) in the register packet when the packet is sent over the register interface. For all other (non-register) interfaces its set to false.

usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinEndTimer.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinEndTimer
usdPimMRouteNextHopJoinEndTimer.description: This object indicates the time (in seconds) left when the join timer expires for the outgoing interface. Join timer for an outgoing interface of <S, G> entry indicates when the <S, G> join expires, for a <*, G> entry indicates when the <*, G> join expires and for a <*, *, RP> entry indicates when the <*, *, RP> join expires. Inherited joins (like <S, G> inheriting from <*, G> AND <*, G> inheriting from <*, *, RP>) expire when the corresponding parent join expires.

usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertEndTimer.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertEndTimer
usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertEndTimer.description: This object indicates the time (in seconds) left when the assert timer expires on this outgoing inteface.

usdPimMRouteNextHopNextAssertTimer.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopNextAssertTimer
usdPimMRouteNextHopNextAssertTimer.description: This object indicates the duration (in seconds) left for which sending an assert has been suppressed on this outgoing interface.

usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertSrcAddress.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertSrcAddress
usdPimMRouteNextHopAssertSrcAddress.description: This object indicates the source address which will be used in the assert packet to send an assert out for the entry on this outgoing interface. For <S, G> entries it is the address of the source S itself. For <*, G> entries it is the address of the source whose data was forwarded using this <*, G> and caused the assert situation to happen.

usdPimMRouteNextHopRegisterSuppressionTi.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopRegisterSuppressionTimer
usdPimMRouteNextHopRegisterSuppressionTi.description: This object is used for register outgoing interfaces. It indicates the duration (in seconds) left for which sending a register packet has been suppressed on the register outgoing interface as a result of receiving register-stop from the RP.

usdPimMRouteNextHopPimType.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopPimType
usdPimMRouteNextHopPimType.description: This object indicates whether the outgoing interface was contributed by sparse-mode or dense-mode PIM.

usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneTimeLeft.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneTimeLeft
usdPimMRouteNextHopPruneTimeLeft.description: This object indicates the time (in seconds) left when the prune timer expires on an outgoing inteface. Its used for pruned outgoing interfaces contributed by dense-mode PIM.

usdPimMRouteNextHopsendingIpAddress.name: usdPimMRouteNextHopsendingIpAddress
usdPimMRouteNextHopsendingIpAddress.description: This object describes the source IP address used by this interface to send PIM packets out on this outgoing interface.

usdPimRPSetTable.name: usdPimRPSetTable
usdPimRPSetTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing enterprise specific information on a subset of the rows of the pimRPSetTable defined in the standard PIM MIB.

usdPimRPSetEntry.name: usdPimRPSetEntry
usdPimRPSetEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimRPSetTable.

usdPimRPSetPriority.name: usdPimRPSetPriority
usdPimRPSetPriority.description: This object describes the priority of the RP for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimRPSetTypeInfo.name: usdPimRPSetTypeInfo
usdPimRPSetTypeInfo.description: This object describes the mechanism by which this group to RP mapping has been learnt, i.e. whether its statically configured, AutoRP learnt or BSR learnt. It also indicates whether the mapping is positive or negative. Negative mappings force the groups in that range to fall into dense-mode category if sparse-dense mode is configured or no RP if its purely sparse mode configuration.

usdPimRPSetAccessListName.name: usdPimRPSetAccessListName
usdPimRPSetAccessListName.description: This object lists the name of the access list from which this group-to-RP mapping was picked up in case of statically configured RPs.

usdPimStaticRPConfTable.name: usdPimStaticRPConfTable
usdPimStaticRPConfTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing statically configured PIM RPs.

usdPimStaticRPConfEntry.name: usdPimStaticRPConfEntry
usdPimStaticRPConfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimStaticRPConfTable.

usdPimStaticRPConfComponentIndex.name: usdPimStaticRPConfComponentIndex
usdPimStaticRPConfComponentIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the component. Each protocol instance connected to a separate domain should have a different index value.

usdPimStaticRPConfRPAddr.name: usdPimStaticRPConfRPAddr
usdPimStaticRPConfRPAddr.description: Ip address of the RP which for the group-to-RP mapping being configured.

usdPimStaticRPConfAccessListName.name: usdPimStaticRPConfAccessListName
usdPimStaticRPConfAccessListName.description: Name of the access list from which group-ranges are picked up for this group-ro-RP mapping. Every deny component in the list is added as negative group-ro-RP mapping.

usdPimStaticRPConfRowStatus.name: usdPimStaticRPConfRowStatus
usdPimStaticRPConfRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

usdPimStaticRPConfOverride.name: usdPimStaticRPConfOverride
usdPimStaticRPConfOverride.description: The object indicates whether or not this statically configured group-to-RP mapping should override the group-to-RP mapping learnt via AutoRP for the component group-ranges in the access list. By default AutoRP learnt group-to-RP mappings are preferred over statically configured ones. While setting the rowStatus to create a static RP, this field should be assigned to true if the override property is desired.

usdPimAutoRPConfTable.name: usdPimAutoRPConfTable
usdPimAutoRPConfTable.description: The (conceptual) table allowing AutoRP configuration of candidate RPs (advertisement agents).

usdPimAutoRPConfEntry.name: usdPimAutoRPConfEntry
usdPimAutoRPConfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimAutoRPConfTable.

usdPimAutoRPConfComponentIndex.name: usdPimAutoRPConfComponentIndex
usdPimAutoRPConfComponentIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the component. Each protocol instance connected to a separate domain should have a different index value.

usdPimAutoRPConfCandRPAddr.name: usdPimAutoRPConfCandRPAddr
usdPimAutoRPConfCandRPAddr.description: The IP address of the candidate RP for this advertising agent configuration.

usdPimAutoRPConfGroupAccessListName.name: usdPimAutoRPConfGroupAccessListName
usdPimAutoRPConfGroupAccessListName.description: The access list name from which group ranges are picked up for advertising agent configuration.

usdPimAutoRPConfRowStatus.name: usdPimAutoRPConfRowStatus
usdPimAutoRPConfRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

usdPimAutoRPConfTTL.name: usdPimAutoRPConfTTL
usdPimAutoRPConfTTL.description: The time-to-live value used while sending AutoRP advertisement out for this group-to-RP mappings created as a result of this configuration. This should be set along with usdPimAutoRPConfRowStatus while creating an AutoRP advertising agent to denote the TTL value to be used.

usdPimAutoRPConfAncmntIntvl.name: usdPimAutoRPConfAncmntIntvl
usdPimAutoRPConfAncmntIntvl.description: The time interval at which AutoRP advertisements are sent out for the group-to-RP mappings created as a result of this configuration. This should be set along with usdPimAutoRPConfRowStatus while creating an AutoRP advertising agent to denote the announcement interval to be used.

usdPimAutoRPConfifId.name: usdPimAutoRPConfifId
usdPimAutoRPConfifId.description: The interface index of the interface for the candidate RP if an interface with that address exists else it is set to 0.

usdPimAutoRPCandTable.name: usdPimAutoRPCandTable
usdPimAutoRPCandTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing AutoRP candidate RPS (advertising agents).

usdPimAutoRPCandEntry.name: usdPimAutoRPCandEntry
usdPimAutoRPCandEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimAutoRPCandTable.

usdPimAutoRPCandComponentIndex.name: usdPimAutoRPCandComponentIndex
usdPimAutoRPCandComponentIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the component. Each protocol instance connected to a separate domain should have a different index value.

usdPimAutoRPCandRPAddr.name: usdPimAutoRPCandRPAddr
usdPimAutoRPCandRPAddr.description: The IP address of the candidate RP for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimAutoRPCandGroupAddr.name: usdPimAutoRPCandGroupAddr
usdPimAutoRPCandGroupAddr.description: The group address of the candidate RP for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimAutoRPCandGroupMask.name: usdPimAutoRPCandGroupMask
usdPimAutoRPCandGroupMask.description: The group mask of the candidate RP for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimAutoRPCandRowStatus.name: usdPimAutoRPCandRowStatus
usdPimAutoRPCandRowStatus.description: The current status of this row.

usdPimAutoRPCandAccessListName.name: usdPimAutoRPCandAccessListName
usdPimAutoRPCandAccessListName.description: The name of the group list using which this AutoRP group-to-RP candidate RP mapping was configured.

usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPTTL.name: usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPTTL
usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPTTL.description: The time-to-live value used while sending AutoRP advertisement out for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPAncmntIntvl.name: usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPAncmntIntvl
usdPimAutoRPCandAutoRPAncmntIntvl.description: The time interval at which AutoRP advertisements are sent out for this group-to-RP mapping.

usdPimAutoRPCandIfId.name: usdPimAutoRPCandIfId
usdPimAutoRPCandIfId.description: The interface index of the interface for this AutoRP group-to-RP candidate RP mapping if an interface for RP address exists else it is set to 0.

usdPimComponentTable.name: usdPimComponentTable
usdPimComponentTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing each component (domain) in PIM.

usdPimComponentEntry.name: usdPimComponentEntry
usdPimComponentEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdPimComponentTable.

usdPimComponentIndex.name: usdPimComponentIndex
usdPimComponentIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the component. Each protocol instance connected to a separate domain should have a different index value.

usdPimComponentAutoRPMappingAgentRowStat.name: usdPimComponentAutoRPMappingAgentRowStatus
usdPimComponentAutoRPMappingAgentRowStat.description: The status of AutoRP mapping agent by which this router can be made an AutoRP mapping agent or removed from being an AutoRP mapping agent in this component.
